.SH "NAME"
modbus_connect \- establish a Modbus connection
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBint modbus_connect(modbus_t *\fR\fB\fIctx\fR\fR\fB);\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
The \fBmodbus_connect()\fR function shall establish a connection to a Modbus server, a network or a bus using the context information of libmodbus context given in argument\&.
.SH "RETURN VALUE"
.sp
The function shall return 0 if successful\&. Otherwise it shall return \-1 and set errno to one of the values defined by the system calls of the underlying platform\&.
.SH "EXAMPLE"
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
modbus_t *ctx;

ctx = modbus_new_tcp("127\&.0\&.0\&.1", 502);
if (modbus_connect(ctx) == \-1) {
    fprintf(stderr, "Connection failed: %s\en", modbus_strerror(errno));
    modbus_free(ctx);
    return \-1;
}
.fi
